style='font-family:Foreign1'>n</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>a.
To be mindful of the three characteristics of existence constitutes the seed of
vijj</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>. Even hunters and fishermen
should be encouraged to practise the advertence of mind. They should not be
told that it is improper for hunters and fishermen to practise advertence of
mind towards samatha (calm) and vipassan</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
(insight). On the other hand, they should be helped towards better
understanding, should they be in difficulties. They should be urged and
encouraged to keep on trying. They are in that stage when even the work of
accumulating p</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ram</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
and tendencies is to be extolled. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h4><a name="_Toc133723522"></a><a name="_Toc133724035"><span style='mso-bookmark:
_Toc133723522'><span lang=EN-US>Loss of Opportunity to Attain the Seed of vijj</span></span></a><span
style='mso-bookmark:_Toc133724035'><span style='mso-bookmark:_Toc133723522'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US> Through
Ignorance of the Value of the Present Times</span></span></span></h4>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Some teachers, who are aware only of the
existence of direct and unequivocal statements in the P</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>al</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>i
Texts regarding the order of practice of the seven visuddhi (purifications),
but who take no account of the value of the present times, say that in the
practices of samatha and vipassan</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> (calm
and insight) no results can be achieved unless s</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la-visuddhi
(purification of virtue) is first fulfilled, whatever be the intensity of the
effort. Some of the uninformed ordinary folk are beguiled by such statements.
Thus has dhammantaraya (danger to the dhamma) occurred. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt'><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>These
persons, because they do not know the nature of the present times, will lose
the opportunity to attain the seeds of vija which are attainable only when a
Buddha S</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>san</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
is encountered. In truth, they have not yet attained release from worldly ills
and are still drifting in sa</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>m</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>s</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ra
(round of rebirths) because, though they have occasionally encountered Buddha S</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>san</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>s
in their past inconceivably long sa</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
Foreign1'>m</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ra where Buddha S</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>san</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>s more numerous than the grains of sands
on the banks of the Ganges had appeared, they did not acquire the foundation of
the seeds of vijj</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt'><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>When
seeds are spoken of, there are seeds ripe or mature enough to sprout into
healthy and strong seedlings, and there are many degrees of ripeness or
maturity. There are also seeds that are unripe or immature. People who do not
know the meanings of the passages they recite or who do not know the right
methods of practice even though they know the meaning, and who thus by custom
or tradition read, recite and count their beads while performing the work of
contemplating the noble qualities of the Buddha, and anicca, dukkha and anatta,
possess seeds that are unripe and immature. These unripe seeds may be ripened
and matured by the continuation of such work in the existences that follow, if
opportuntity for such continued work occurs. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt'><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>The
practice of samatha until the appearance of parikamma- nimitta,<a
style='mso-footnote-id:ftn34' href="#_ftn34" name="_ftnref34" title=""><span
class=MsoFootnoteReference><span style='background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow;
mso-shading:yellow'><span style='mso-special-character:footnote'><![if !supportFootnotes]>[34]<![endif]></span></span></span></a><span
style='background:yellow'> </span>and the practice of vipassan</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> until insight is obtained into r</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>u</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>pa and n</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ma
(matter and mind) even once, are mature seeds filled with pith and substance.
The practice of samatha until the appearance of uggaha-nimitta and the practice
of vipassan</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> until the acquisition of
sammasana</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>ban</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>a<a style='mso-footnote-id:
ftn35' href="#_ftn35" name="_ftnref35" title=""><span
class=MsoFootnoteReference><span style='background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow;
mso-shading:yellow'><span style='mso-special-character:footnote'><![if !supportFootnotes]>[35]<![endif]></span></span></span></a>
even once, are seeds that are still more mature. The practice of samatha until
the appearance of pa</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>t</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ibh</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ga-nimitt</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>, and the practice of vipassan</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> until the occurrence of udayabbaya</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>ban</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>a <a style='mso-footnote-id:ftn36'
href="#_ftn36" name="_ftnref36" title=""><span class=MsoFootnoteReference><span
style='background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow;mso-shading:yellow'><span
style='mso-special-character:footnote'><![if !supportFootnotes]>[36]<![endif]></span></span></span></a><span
style='background:yellow'> </span>even once, are seeds that are yet more
extremely mature. If further higher effort can be made in both samatha and
vipassan</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>, still more mature seeds can
be obtained bringing great success. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h4><a name="_Toc133723523"></a><a name="_Toc133724036"><span style='mso-bookmark:
_Toc133723523'><span lang=EN-US>Adhik</span></span></a><span style='mso-bookmark:
