<h4><a name="_Toc133723535"></a><a name="_Toc133724042"><span style='mso-bookmark:
_Toc133723535'><span lang=EN-US>Uppanna And Anuppanna Akusala Kamma</span></span></a></h4>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>In the personality of every
being wandering in sa</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>m</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>s</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ra
(round of rebirths) there are two kinds of akusala kamma (unwholesome
volitional actions), namely: <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul type=disc>
 <ol start=13 type=1>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:
      auto;mso-list:l2 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 72.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
      style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>uppanna akusala kamma <o:p></o:p></span></li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:
      auto;mso-list:l2 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 72.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
      style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>anuppanna akusala kamma. <o:p></o:p></span></li>
 </ol>
</ul>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Uppanna akusala kamma means past and
present akusala kamma. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>They comprise unwholesome volitional
actions committed in the interminable series of past world-cycles and past
lives. Among these akusala kamma, there are some that have spent themselves by
having produced rebirths in the apaya-loka. There are others that await the
opportunity of producing rebirths in the apaya-loka, and thus constitute
potentialities for rebirth in the apaya-loka that accompany beings from
world-cycle to world-cycle and from life to life. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Every being in whom sakk</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ya-di</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>tt</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>hi
(personality-belief) resides, be he a human being, or a deva, or a Brahma,
possesses an infinitely large store of such past debts, so to say, consisting
of akusala kamma (unwholesome volitional actions) that have in thein the
potentiality of producing rebirths in the lowest Avici Hell. Similarly, there
are infinite stores of other kamma capable of producing rebirths in the other
apaya-loka. These past kamma which await a favourable opportunity for producing
rebirth resultants and which accompany beings from life to life until they are
expended, are called uppanna. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>These past uppanna akusala kamma have
their roots in sakk</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ya-di</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>tt</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>hi
(personality-belief). As long as sakk</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
