<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>This class of lokuttara-s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la is achieved only when anatta-bh</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>van</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
is successfully practised. Beings must attempt to achieve this anuppana-s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la while yet within a Buddha S</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>san</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>.
It is meant by this that from the moment of setting up s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la-visuddhi (together with k</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>yagata-sati) up to the successful
completion of anatta-bh</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>van</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>,
beings must attempt (without relaxation) to practise the thirty-seven
bodhipakkhiya-dhamma. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Uppanna-s</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la,
which has often occurred in past infinite sa</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>m</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ra, means lokiya-s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la or k</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>mavac</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ra-s</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la.[72]
When it is said that attempt must be made to attain the state of fixation of
that s</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la, it must be understood that
there are two planes of lokiya-s</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la:
niyama and aniyama.[73] The state of an ariya is that of the niyama plane,
while the state of a puthujjana is that of the aniyama plane. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>The kam</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>vacara-lokiya-s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la attains the niyama plane in the
personalities of sotapannas. Ariyas who are sotapannas do not transgress the </span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>j</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>va</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>tt</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>hamaka-s</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la
even in their dreams throughout the series of lives and world cycles that
follow until the final attainment of Parinibb</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>na.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>In the case of puthujjana, however, the k</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>mavacara-lokiya-s</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la
is still in the aniyama plane. These persons have been virtuous and moral lay
individuals on an infinite number of occasions in the past. They have also
suffered in the apaya loka countless number of times. They have been virtuous
Isis and bhikkhus on other infinite number of occasions. In all their past
existences, however, they have never been free from the danger of liability to
rebirth in the apaya loka. Even now, the number of beings in the apaya loka is
infinite and the number of humans, devas and Brahmas, on the brink of being
born in the apaya loka is infinite. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Hence, beings possessing k</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>mavacara-lokiya-s</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la,
which is still aniyama, and which, so to say, resides in them for a temporary
moment, should attempt, while there is yet opportunity within a Buddha S</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>san</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>,
to transform it into niyama. They should set up k</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>yagata-sati,
and having done so, should practise the bodhipakkhiya-dhamma until the function
of anatta-bh</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>van</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
is successfully completed. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>This completes the two s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la kusala kamma. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h4><a name="_Toc133723538"></a><a name="_Toc133724045"><span style='mso-bookmark:
_Toc133723538'><span lang=EN-US>Uppanna And Anuppanna Sam</span></span></a><span
style='mso-bookmark:_Toc133724045'><span style='mso-bookmark:_Toc133723538'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US>dhi</span></span></span></h4>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Sam</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi
also has two planes: niyama and aniyama. Similarly, there are two planes of pa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>bba</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>: niyama and aniyama. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Appan</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-sam</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi, which is identical with the eight or
nine samapatti[74] as the case may be, becomes niyama only when one attains the
an</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>g</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>m</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> stage. The pa</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>bba</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
"Times New Roman"'> that carries the tadi[75] quality becomes niyama only at the
stage of an arahant. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>I shall now show the samadhi and pa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>bba</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> that sotapannas achieve. In accordance
with the discourse in the Mah</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> Vedalla Sutta,[76] wherein it
is said: <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Yo ca visakha samm</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-vayamo ya ca samm</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-sati yo ca samm</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-sam</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi, ime dhamma samadhikkhandhe sa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>gahita. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Samm</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-v</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>y</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ma
(right effort), samm</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a-</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>sati (right mindfulness) and
samm</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-sam</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi
(right concentration), which are comprised within sotapatti-magga (path of a
stream-winner) having Nibb</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>na as object, are called
lokuttara-sam</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi (supramundane
concentration). <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>These three sam</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi
can extinguish, once and for all, that is by samuccheda-pahana,[77] the mental
evils of abhijjha (covetousness) and byapada (ill-will), which have miccha-v</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>y</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ma
(wrong effort), miccha-sati (wrong mindfulness), and miccha-sam</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi (wrong concentration), as their
roots. From the instant they are extinguished, the mental evils of abhijjha and
byapada do not arise again throughout the many lives and world-cycles that may
follow. It is the kind of sam</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi that can be achieved only
within a Buddha S</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>san</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>,
when only appears anatta-bh</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>van</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>.
Hence, now that they have encountered a Buddha S</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>san</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>, beings should endeavour to achieve
anuppanna-sam</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi without fail, before they
become severed from the S</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>san</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>.
This means that, beginning with k</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>yagata-sati,
they should practise the bodhipakkhiya-dhamma until they attain the successful
culmination of anatta-bh</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>van</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Upanna-sam</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi,
which has occurred countless number of times in infinite past sa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>m</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>s</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ra,
consists of k</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>mavacara-sam</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi, r</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>u</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>pavacara-sam</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi and ar</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>u</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>pavacara-sam</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi. When it is said that attempt must be
made to make uppanna-samadhi niyama, it must be understood that there are two
planes in lokiya-sam</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi: niyama and aniyama. The
lokiya-samm</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-v</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>y</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ma, samm</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-sati
and samm</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-sam</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi,
with which ariyas are endowed, are established in the niyama plane. The ducc</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>rita such as abhijja and byapada do not
arise in them even in dreams throughout the succession of lives and
world-cycles that follow until the final attainment of Parinibb</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>na. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>The group of lokiya-sam</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi with which puthujjana are endowed is
in the aniyama plane. In the infinite past sa</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>m</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ra, these persons have been men of sam</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi, Isis of sam</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi,
and bhikkhus of sam</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi, endowed with jh</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>na and powers, such as the ability to fly
through the air or go through the earth, during an infinite number of
existences. In the life-period of every world-system, there are four kappa
(world-cycles), each of infinite length. In three of these kappa, these
puthujjana have been Brahmas in the brahma-loka. In every one of these
world-systems, there have also appeared the apaya loka. These apaya loka have
been filled by these self-same Brahmas and no other. These puthujjana have been
Brahmas, petas, beings of hell, animals and asuras. In the infinitely long sa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>m</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>s</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ra,
the life-period of each of these world-systems is like but the period of the
twinkling of an eye. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Thus, it behaves us all to endeavour to
transform the aniyama lokiya samm</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-v</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>y</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ma,
samm</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-sati and samm</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-sam</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>dhi
(which we temporarily acquired in the past on many countless occasions) to
niyama, while there is yet opportunity now when we are in the midst of a Buddha
S</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>san</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>.
We must, after first setting up k</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>yagata-sati,
practise the bodhipakkhiya-dhamma until the successful completion of anatta-bh</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>van</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>This ends the two samadhi kusala kamma. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h4><a name="_Toc133723539"></a><a name="_Toc133724046"><span style='mso-bookmark:
_Toc133723539'><span lang=EN-US>Uppanna And Anuppanna Pa</span></span></a><span
style='mso-bookmark:_Toc133724046'><span style='mso-bookmark:_Toc133723539'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>bba</span></span></span></h4>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>In accordance with the
discourse in the Mah</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> Vedalla Sutta, wherein it is
said: <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Ya ca visakha samm</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-di</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>tt</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>hi
yo ca samm</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-sa</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>kappo
ime dhamma pannakkhandhe sa</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span
