<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Catusaccadhamme sutthu bujjhatitti
sambodhi. Sambodhiya ango sa</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>m</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>bojjha</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>go.
(Can clearly perceive the Four Noble Truths. Hence called sambodhi. Constituent
of magga-</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>ban</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>a. Hence called sa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>m</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>bojjha</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ga.)
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Birds are first delivered from their mothers'
wombs in the form of eggs. They are then delivered a second time by breaking
the eggs. Thence, when they become full fledged with feathers and wings, they
are delivered from their nests, when they can fly wherever they please. In the
same way, in the case of yogavac</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ra
individuals, they are first delivered from the distractions of mind which have
accompanied them through infinite sa</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
Foreign1'>m</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ra when they successfully set up k</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>yagata-sati or accomplish the work of
samatha. Secondly, when they attain vipassan</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
insight into r</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>u</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>pa, n</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ma-khandha,
etc., they are free from coarse forms of ignorance. Finally, when the seven
bojjha</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ga develop and mature, they
become full fledged in lokuttara-magga-</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>ban</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
"Times New Roman"'>a, and attain the magga-</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>ban</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
"Times New Roman"'>a known as sambodhi, and thus they are delivered from the
state of worldlings. They are delivered from the state of puthujjana and attain
the state of ariya--of lokuttara or Nibb</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>na.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>There are seven bojjha</span><span
