style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>veti,
viveka nissita</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>m</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>, viraga nissita</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>m</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>, nirodha nissita</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>m</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>,
vossaggaparinami</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>m</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>.[132] <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>It does not refer to s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la that has leanings towards
bhava-sampatti and dependency on the round of rebirths. The s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la-visuddhi of those who have consciously
given up attempts at attaining the holy Paths and the Fruits in this life is
not genuine adibrahmacariyaka-s</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la [133] and thus is not of
the genuine bodhipakkhiya class. If effort be made, however, towards the attainment
of Nibb</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>na in the next life, it can be
p</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ram</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la which is a part of vivatta nissita-s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>samm</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-v</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>c</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>,
samm</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-kammanta, and samma-</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>j</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>va
magga</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ga are purely of the class of
s</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la and hence constitute genuine s</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la-visuddhi They are also called the three
virati cetasika.'[134] <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Samm</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-sa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>kappa is vitakka-cetasika. Since it is
the harbinger of pa</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>bba</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>, it is included in the pa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>bba</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> category. There are three kinds of sa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>kappa, namely nekkhama-sa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>kappa, abyapada-sa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>kappa, and avihimsa-sa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>kappa. Just as a person incarcerated in
prison, or a person beseiged by enemy troops, or a person encircled by a forest
fire, or a fish caught in a net, tank, or trap, or a bird caught in a cage, is
absorbed (without being able to sleep or eat) in only only one thought, that is
in the attempt to escape from these confinements, the attempts of those persons
who contrive with sammappadh</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>n</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>-v</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>riya to escape, from the confinement of
the old infinitely numerous uppanna-akusala kamma and the new infinitely
numerous anuppanna-akusala-kamma that are due to arise are called nekkhama-sa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>kappa magga</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ga.
It is the sort of sa</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>kappa which looks for the way
to escape in this very life from the vattadukkha (round of rebirths). <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>The sa</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>kappa
which associates with mett</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> jh</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>na
is called abyapada-sa</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>kappa. The sa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>kappa which associates with karu</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>na</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> jh</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>na
is called avihimsa-sa</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>kappa. The sa</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>kappa which associates with the remaining
jh</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>na is called
nekkhama-sahkappa. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

