<h3 style='tab-stops:24.0pt'><a name="_Toc133723565"></a><a name="_Toc133724054"><span
style='mso-bookmark:_Toc133723565'><span lang=EN-US>IX, How to practise The
Bodhipakkhiya-Dhamma</span></span></a></h3>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='margin-left:36.0pt;text-align:center;
tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'><img
width=466 height=3 id="_x0000_i2372"
src="9-THE%20MANUALS%20OF%20BUDDHISM,Bodhipakkhiya%20Dipani,IX.files\Bar.gif"><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Beings who encounter a Buddha S</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>san</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
have to set up s</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la-visuddhi first and practise
the bodhipakkhiya dhamma in order to attain the status of ariya-sota. I shall
now give a brief description of how the practice may be undertaken. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>The practice of the seven-visuddhi
amounts to practising the bodhi- pakkhiya-dhamma. In particular, citta-visuddi
concerns only persons who follow the way of the samatha-yanika. Maggamagga-</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>ban</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>adassana- visuddhi concerns only those
adhimanika persons[146] who think that they have attained the holy Paths and
the Fruits although they have achieved no such attainment. S</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la-visuddhi, ka</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>khavitarana-visuddhi,
patipada-</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>ban</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>adassana-visuddhi, and
lokuttara-</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>ban</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>adassana-visuddhi, relate to
many kinds of persons. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Of these five visuddhi, sila-visuddhi has
been dealt with under s</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>lakkhandha- magga</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>v</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ga. It consists of keeping the </span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>j</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>va</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>tt</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>hamaka-s</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>la
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Citta-visuddhi, in general, consists of
setting up k</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>yagata-sati. Some persons set
up k</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>yagata-sati through out-breath
and in-breath. It may be said generally that if one¡¦s attention resides on out-
breath and in-breath, whenever one wills it, no matter what the posture of the
body may be, k</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>yagata-sati has been set up.
Some persons set up k</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>yagata-sati through the four
body postures in accordance with the statement in the text[147]: 'gaccanto
gacchamiti pajanati', while others set it up through sati-sampajanna (clearness
of consciousness) on bodily movements. Yet others set up k</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>yagata-sati through attention on the
thirty-two parts of the body. Here, hairs of the head, hairs of the body,
nails, teeth, and skin, are called tacapancaka[148] If attention on these parts
can be firmly and steadily placed at will, whatever may be the postures of the
body, k</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>yagata-sati is set up. Attention
can also be directed to the bones of the body. K</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>yagata-sati
is set up if attention can be steadily and firmly placed on the bones of the
head. If, from the beginning, the r</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
Foreign1'>u</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>pa and
n</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ma groups of the body can be analytically
differentiated, and if attention on such work is steady and firm, the work of k</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>yagata-sati is accomplished. This gives
concisely the method of k</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>yagata-sati. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>In the work of di</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>tt</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>hi-visuddhi,
if the six elements (dhatu) of pa</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
Foreign1'>t</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>hav</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>, apo, tejo, vayo, akasa, and vinnana,
can be analytically perceived, it is accomplished. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>In the work of khankkha-vitarana
visuddhi, if the causes for the appearance of the dhatu mentioned above can be
clearly perceived, it is accomplished. It must be clearly perceived that the
causes for the appearance of pa</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>t</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>hav</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>,
apo, tejo, vayo and akasa are kammna, citta, uttu, and ahara, and that the
causes for the appearance of the six vinnana are the six objects of perception.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>By pa</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>t</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ipada-</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>ban</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>adassana-visuddhi is meant the three
characteristics of anicca, dukkha, and anatta. If these three characteristics
can be clearly perceived in the six dhatu mentioned above, patipada-</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>ban</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>adassana visuddhi is attained. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Lokuttara-</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>ban</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
"Times New Roman"'>adassana-visuddhi means the four magga-</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>ban</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>a. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>This shows concisely the visuddhi. For a
more detailed account see my Lakkha</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
Foreign1'>n</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>a D</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>pan</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>,
Vijj</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>magga D</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>pan</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>,
and </span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>A</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>h</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ra
D</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>pan</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>i</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>These thirty-seven bodhipakkhiya-dhamma
are the heritages of the Buddha. They are the heritages of the S</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>san</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>.
They constitute gems of the S</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>san</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
that are priceless and invaluable. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='margin-left:36.0pt;text-align:center;
tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'><img
