he is an ariya (brahmana), he is a bhikkhu.] <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>This passage shows that a person who
practises the dhammdnudhamma- patipatti, which are the bodhipakkhiya-dhamma,
and lives with pure mind and body, can be called a bhikkhu even though he dons
the clothes of an ordinary layman. This shows the nobility and high status of
the heirs of the S</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>san</span><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:Foreign1'>a</span><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p style='margin-left:36.0pt;tab-stops:24.0pt'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>In the matter of heritages of the S</span><span
